{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἕδνον</b>, τό, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 9.10, 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Fragmenta” 193, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 25.114, 27.33, 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Argonautica” 873, 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 42.28, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; elsewhere only <i>plural</i> <b>ἕδνα</b>, <b>ἔεδνα</b>:— <b>bride-price</b> or <b>wedding-gifts</b> (φερνή being the bride's <b>portion</b>), ὄπυιε πορὼν ἀπερείσια ἕ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.178; ἠγάγετο.. ἐπεὶ πόρε μυρία ἕ. [prev. work] 190, compare 22.472; μνάσθω ἐέδνοισιν διζήμενος 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 16.391; εἰς ὅ κέ μοι.. πατὴρ ἀποδῷσιν ἔεδνα 8.318 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; rare in Trag., ἕδνοις ἄγαγες Ἡσιόναν πιθὼν δάμαρτα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 559 (Lyric poetry): later Prose, 1st c.BC: Parthenius Mythographus 20.1. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>wedding-gifts</b> made to the bride <b>by those of her own household</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.277, 2.196, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 2, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 9.10 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; but, <br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “P.” 3.94, Orph.[same place], 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 79.12 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>], <b>wedding-presents</b> to a wedded pair <b>by their guests.</b> <br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> generally, <b>gift</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 25.114. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7044","accentedUnicode":"ἔδνα","shortDef":"a dowry","mediumDef":"a dowry","stepGloss":"a dowry","stepTransliteration":"edna","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}